title: What Is a User Report
chunk_text: An Amstat user report is a report created within the settings feature. This report outlines the total number of users on a subscription and their activity.

metadata.topic: Definition and Purpose of Amstat User Report

title: What Is a User Report
chunk_text: The user activity report can be found under My Account and Settings, specifically under User Activity. The admin has the ability to download this report.

metadata.topic: Locating and Accessing the User Activity Report

title: What Is a User Report
chunk_text: The report includes information from all current subscribers, such as when they last used the service, when they first used the service, their level of service, and login sessions over the last couple of months.

metadata.topic: Details and Data Included in the User Activity Report
